"{\"uid\": \"wsmv.com-2024-06-17-nashvilles-gretchen-walsh-qualifies-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"NASHVILLE, Tenn. (WSMV) - Nashville swimmer Gretchen Walsh has qualified for the Olympics after winning the 100-meter butterfly race at Sunday's U.S. Olympic Trials at Lucas Oil Stadium.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 186, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 9, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nashville_Superspeedway\", \"score\": 0.8270594751661708, \"rank\": 0.20881253071723394, \"text\": \"NASHVILLE\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nashville_Superspeedway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nashville_Superspeedway\"}, {\"begin\": 26, \"end\": 35, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nashville_Superspeedway\", \"score\": 0.8270594751661708, \"rank\": 0.20881253071723394, \"text\": \"Nashville\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nashville_Superspeedway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nashville_Superspeedway\"}, {\"begin\": 44, \"end\": 58, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gretchen Walsh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Walsh earned her first trip to the Olympics by winning Sunday's finals in a time of 55.31, the second-fastest time in history.\", \"from\": 188, \"to\": 314, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was just off the world record pace she set in Saturday's semifinal heat.\", \"from\": 315, \"to\": 390, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am still in shock.\", \"from\": 392, \"to\": 413, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Making the team was the biggest goal,\\\" Walsh said in an interview after the race.\", \"from\": 414, \"to\": 495, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Getting the world record was absolutely insane.\\\"\", \"from\": 496, \"to\": 545, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In Nashville, Walsh swims for the Nashville Aquatic Club.\", \"from\": 547, \"to\": 604, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 550, \"end\": 559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nashville_Superspeedway\", \"score\": 0.8270594751661708, \"rank\": 0.20881253071723394, \"text\": \"Nashville\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nashville_Superspeedway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nashville_Superspeedway\"}, {\"begin\": 581, \"end\": 590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nashville_Superspeedway\", \"score\": 0.8270594751682394, \"rank\": 0.20881253071723394, \"text\": \"Nashville\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nashville_Superspeedway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nashville_Superspeedway\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Walsh set the world record in Saturday's semifinal heat posting a time of 55.18, eclipsing the record set at the 2016 Rio de Janeiro Olympics.\", \"from\": 606, \"to\": 748, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gretchen's sister Alex won a silver medal at the Tokyo Olympics in 2021.\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 822, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 750, \"end\": 758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9321324714345195e-15, \"text\": \"Gretchen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both sisters will be competing throughout the trials.\", \"from\": 823, \"to\": 876, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Alex qualified for Monday's final in the 100 meter breaststroke with a third place finish in Sunday's semifinal.\", \"from\": 878, \"to\": 990, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright 2024 WSMV.\", \"from\": 992, \"to\": 1012, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All rights reserved.\